     NNNNaaaammmmeeee
          WC - Counts the characters, words and lines in a file.

     SSSSyyyynnnnttttaaaaxxxx
          wwwwcccc [ ----ccccwwwwllllpppp!!!!????hhhh ] [ _w_i_l_d_s_p_e_c ][ :_d_r_i_v_e_s_p_e_c ]...
          [<<<< _f_i_l_e | _d_e_v_i_c_e ] [>>>>[>>>>] _f_i_l_e | _d_e_v_i_c_e ] [ ; _n_e_x_t _c_o_m_m_a_n_d ]

     DDDDeeeessssccccrrrriiiippppttttiiiioooonnnn
          _W_c reads the contents of the specified files and reports on
          the number of characters, words and lines that each file
          contains.  When more than one file is examined, a total is
          also displayed.

          _W_c accepts several options.  Options are specified by single
          characters, and they may be entered in upper or lowercase.
          Options are always preceded by a hyphen (a "-").  If you are
          specifying multiple options, you can specify the options in
          any of these formats:
                -a -b -c   or   -abc   or   -a -bc   or  -ab -c

          The options are:

          ----cccc   Displays the number of characters present in the file.

          ----wwww   Displays the number of words present in the file.
               Words are considered to be blank- or carriage-control-
               separated groups of characters.

          ----llll   Displays the number of lines present in the file.  _W_c
               counts the sequence 0x0d 0x0a (CR/LF) as a single line,
               but all other combinations of 0x0d and/or 0x0a are
               counted as two lines.

          ----pppp   Output of _w_c is routed through the _m_o_r_e(U1) utility.
               The screen will pause once 23 lines of text have been
               displayed.  The _m_o_r_e(U1) prompt ("--More--") allows you
               to advance or search through the remainder of the
               output.  See the _m_o_r_e(U1) command for additional
               information on the options that _m_o_r_e(U1) provides.  The
               ----pppp option is ignored if the output is redirected.

          ----!!!!   Causes _w_c to ignore any default settings that are
               specified in the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file.  _W_c will also
               ignore any options that are specified to the left of
               the ----!!!! option.  Note that the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file is
               accessed even if the ----!!!! option is specified.

          ----???? oooorrrr ----hhhh
               Displays the help message.






