          :_d_r_i_v_e_s_p_e_c
               The _d_r_i_v_e_s_p_e_c specifies one or more logical drives that
               should be scanned for files that match the file
               _w_i_l_d_s_p_e_c.  The % and * will examine all enabled drives.
               A range can also be used.  For example, :[2-47] will
               search for files on drives 2, 3, 4 and 7.

               If the _d_r_i_v_e_s_p_e_c is not specified and a _w_i_l_d_s_p_e_c is,
               all drives are searched for files that match the file
               _w_i_l_d_s_p_e_c and all files that match will be displayed.
               So if the command wwwwcccc ssssaaaammmmpppplllleeee////ttttxxxxtttt is used and the file
               SAMPLE/TXT exists on four different logical drives, all
               four files will be examined.


          <<<< _f_i_l_e | _d_e_v_i_c_e
               If a file or device is specified, _w_c will read the data
               from the file or device until the end-of-file is
               detected or an error occurs.  This is known as
               _r_e_d_i_r_e_c_t_e_d _i_n_p_u_t.  For example, if you specify <<<< ****KKKKIIII,
               characters will be read from the keyboard until <BREAK>
               is pressed.  These characters will not be echoed.

               Redirected input will override any wildspecs that are
               specified.


          >>>>[>>>>] _f_i_l_e | _d_e_v_i_c_e
               By specifying a file or device, the output is sent to
               the specified file or device instead of the display.
               This is known as _r_e_d_i_r_e_c_t_e_d _o_u_t_p_u_t.  For example, the
               command wwwwcccc aaaa****::::5555 >>>> ccccoooouuuunnnntttt::::0000 places the size information
               for a list of files from logical drive 5 with names
               that start with the letter 'a' in the file CCCCOOOOUUUUNNNNTTTT::::0000.  If
               >> is used, the output will be appended to any existing
               contents of the file.  _F_i_l_e_s_p_e_c_s for redirection may
               not specify a password.


          ; _n_e_x_t _c_o_m_m_a_n_d
               After _w_c completes, the remainder of the command line
               is executed as a second command.  The command wwwwcccc
               xxxx::::1111;;;;ddddaaaatttteeee will display the size information for the
               specified file, and then the date will be displayed.


          <SHIFT>@
               When pressed during output to the display, the output
               will pause.  Pressing any other key resumes output.
               Pressing this key is ignored when output is redirected.





