     NNNNooootttteeeessss
          When the ----llll, ----wwww, and ----cccc options are used, they are position
          dependent.  The first option specified will have its value
          displayed first.  For example, if you specified ----llllcccc, the
          number of lines would be the first item displayed, followed
          by the number of characters.

          If the same option appears more than once, that information
          is displayed as many times as the option is specified, in
          the order that the options were specified.

          If the ----llll, ----wwww, and ----cccc options are not specified at all, the
          default options ----llllwwwwcccc is used automatically.

          If _w_c is not able to read a file because it is password
          protected, only the character total will be displayed.  The
          fields for line and width will be marked with a "-", and an
          error message will be displayed after the filename to
          indicate what the problem was.

          _W_c accepts filespecs using the "/" or "." to separate the
          filename extension.  Because of this, files with passwords
          cannot be specified.

          _W_c can be run on executable and other non-ASCII files.  The
          character count will always be correct, but the word and
          line count will probably have no relevance.


     FFFFiiiilllleeeessss
          _W_c reads the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file and uses any default options
          that are specified there.  For example, if you wanted _W_c to
          display only the word count, the following entry in the
          DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file would do this:
                      WC -W
          Options in the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file are ignored if the ----!!!!
          option is specified on the command line.

          You may make copies of _w_c with different names.  When
          examining the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file, the name used to invoke the
          program will be used to locate the default entries.  For
          example, if you made copies of WWWWCCCC////CCCCMMMMDDDD and named them
          WWWWOOOORRRRDDDDSSSS////CCCCMMMMDDDD and LLLLIIIINNNNEEEESSSS////CCCCMMMMDDDD, you could add the following lines
          to the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file:
                      WORDS -W
                      LINES -L
          Now, when _w_o_r_d_s is run, only the number of words in the file
          will be displayed, and when _l_i_n_e_s is run, it would just
          display the number of lines in the file.






